<br>
As for your questions.  I strictly used H2H until my 50s (this was due to monks not needing weapons at that time).  As a joke I would pick up an FS hammer or staff and swing it a few times for a chuckle...little did I know.  :/<br>
<br>
Anyway...you should always work on 1hb, 2hb, and your H2H each time you level.  Do not fear though.  It is not difficult to get those skills to increase...just takes a little time.<br>
<br>
If you do a lot of grouping, you can use an H2H weapon (your ulak) and a 1HB weapon at the same time.  This will allow you to get decent damage while working on your skill.  If your group doesn't mind, you can work on 1HB or 2HB solely.  Another option is to take time away from xp and find a group that will allow you to play 7th man (i.e. you hit their mobs for skill increases only...no xp...no loot).<br>
<br>
As for your weapon options...Since you are new and likely have no source of money yet...buy 1HB and 2HB weapons from the vendors...they usually have something dirt cheap and while the damage and delay aren't the great, it will work for now.  As you gain cash flow, you may want to look for a fighting baton and/or black jack for 1HB and a bamboo bo stick (or even a bo stick) for 2HB.<br>
<br>
The catch with most decent weapons is that they require you to be a bit higher than 17 to kill.  Do not fear though.  I was in the same boat at 51 that you are in at 17...you have a big advantage over me...my skills are maxed...so I am confident that your's will be too.  <p><br><br><CENTER>
